message: Starting critique - gathering phase handover and examining deliverables
Examining generated questions file to assess quality, format, and coverage
Critical issue identified: agents reported completion but deliverables not found. Examining agent logs to understand what happened.
Architectural analysis complete. Preparing senior dev critique on deliverable management and integration workflow.

Critique submitted successfully. Identified critical architectural issue: 23 high-quality questions generated but not integrated into week10.json (classic 'last mile' delivery gap). Content quality appears strong - proper differential diagnosis, comprehensive explanations, appropriate difficulty mix. Recommended adding integration/consolidation workflow for future phases. Key observations: (1) Deliverable integration gap, (2) Workflow architecture needs aggregation step, (3) Content quality indicators positive, (4) Format validation missing, (5) Good agent specialization pattern.
